01:34.028 --> 01:36.528
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:39.467 --> 01:42.367
 ANDERSON:
 The afflictions of this world

01:42.369 --> 01:46.138
  became too much
  for Norville Grant to bear,

01:48.142 --> 01:50.642
      so he chose
      to leave them behind,

01:51.812 --> 01:53.979
 sooner than the Lord intended.

01:53.981 --> 01:56.815
       (coughing)
          But he rests easy now,

01:56.817 --> 01:59.651
              reunited with
              his beloved Elise,

01:59.653 --> 02:02.721
            and he is remembered
            by those who...

02:03.891 --> 02:05.557
           who he leaves behind.

02:09.497 --> 02:11.296
                Would you like
                to say anything?

02:14.668 --> 02:16.568
             Uh...

02:19.340 --> 02:20.672
                       Caleb.

02:20.674 --> 02:22.474
  (clears throat)

02:24.945 --> 02:26.512
            (grunts)

02:27.615 --> 02:30.883
    Uh, let me get my tools.

02:32.586 --> 02:33.852
        (quietly) Shit.

02:43.631 --> 02:45.964
Sorry I'm late.

02:45.966 --> 02:48.800
         I-I didn't realize
         anyone else was coming.

02:48.802 --> 02:50.169
                 Are you family?

02:50.171 --> 02:51.937
        No.

02:51.939 --> 02:53.505
Just a friend.

02:55.276 --> 02:58.844
I knew he was struggling
with the loss of Elise,

02:58.846 --> 03:05.384
but... had no idea how
hopeless he must have felt.

03:05.386 --> 03:07.920
              My condolences.
              Reverend Anderson.

03:09.857 --> 03:11.056
            Sidney.

03:11.058 --> 03:12.858
                     Sidney.

03:14.295 --> 03:17.196
Were you
and Norville close?

03:17.198 --> 03:20.832
    Uh, not really. No, sir.

03:20.834 --> 03:22.201
       I lived next door.

03:23.704 --> 03:26.171
You're the young man
who found him.

03:26.173 --> 03:30.309
       Yeah. Kyle Barnes.

03:30.311 --> 03:32.744
SIDNEY:
Norville spoke about you.

03:32.746 --> 03:35.180
     Oh, he did?
Fondly.

03:35.182 --> 03:39.484
I'm gonna be in town
for a while to put
Norville's affairs in order.

03:39.486 --> 03:41.386
I hope I see you around.

03:41.388 --> 03:43.388
          Yeah. Sure.

03:46.827 --> 03:49.795
Goodbye, old friend.

03:54.668 --> 03:56.168
      Reverend.

04:04.845 --> 04:07.913
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:12.786 --> 04:15.787
        (radio playing)

04:19.459 --> 04:24.296
   ♪ These blues
   ain't goin' nowhere fast ♪

04:25.766 --> 04:27.933
 ♪ These blues, they were... ♪

04:27.935 --> 04:30.435
Well, aren't you
the little magpie.

04:30.437 --> 04:32.471
        What's all this?

04:32.473 --> 04:34.206
It's my collection.

04:35.242 --> 04:37.876
         See, it's, uh...

04:37.878 --> 04:40.545
            people I've helped,
            they give me things,

04:40.547 --> 04:42.381
                  little tokens.

04:42.383 --> 04:45.584
        It doesn't feel right
        to throw them out, so...

04:45.586 --> 04:47.419
      Notches on
      your gun belt.

04:47.421 --> 04:49.087
              (chuckles)

04:49.089 --> 04:52.424
            Well, I wouldn't
            say that, but, um...

04:52.426 --> 04:56.395
                they represent
                victories, yeah.

04:56.397 --> 04:58.997
    Now where'd this
    little fella come from?

05:03.504 --> 05:04.736
          (screaming)

05:13.847 --> 05:15.247
Are you all right?

05:16.283 --> 05:18.350
          This one...

05:21.689 --> 05:25.190
 Yeah. Yeah, that was hard-won.

05:26.593 --> 05:28.593
I imagine they all were.

05:28.595 --> 05:33.131
         It's my ex-wife Janet.
         She thought it was sad.

05:33.133 --> 05:37.769
Like an old...
high school quarterback
reliving the glory days.

05:39.773 --> 05:43.208
I don't imagine she'd
think much of my collection.

05:43.210 --> 05:45.777
           I don't really
           care what she thinks.

05:54.455 --> 05:55.821
           Goddammit.

05:55.823 --> 05:57.222
                  You all right?

05:57.224 --> 05:59.991
        Yeah. Zip me up?

05:59.993 --> 06:01.693
                   Mmm.

06:01.695 --> 06:03.695
                    You nervous?

06:03.697 --> 06:06.031
It's date night.
We're not going
to the White House.

06:06.033 --> 06:08.567
       Uh, come on. Date Night's
       a lot of pressure.

06:08.569 --> 06:10.135
          I know I'm feeling it.

06:10.137 --> 06:12.904
      I ran out of things to say
      a long time ago.

06:12.906 --> 06:15.640
          Took me a long time
          to come up with a good
          topic for tonight.

06:15.642 --> 06:18.043
I'll be the judge of that.
                      Mm-hmm.

06:18.045 --> 06:19.878
              Better just
              bring your A-game.

06:19.880 --> 06:21.646
(chuckles)

06:21.648 --> 06:23.348
All I have is A-game.

06:23.350 --> 06:25.350
           (laughing)
        (doorbell rings)

06:25.352 --> 06:26.985
                        Oh.
Will you let the sitter in?

06:26.987 --> 06:28.053
              Yup.

06:41.535 --> 06:44.703
        Okay, you ready
        for the topic
        of conversation tonight?

06:44.705 --> 06:47.672
      (chuckles)
          Wait for it. Vacation.

06:47.674 --> 06:52.344
       By my math,
       I think we could swing
       a week down at the ocean.

06:52.346 --> 06:54.346
       (loud chattering)

06:54.348 --> 06:57.215
     Doug Myer's brother-in-law,
     he's got a house down
     in Myrtle Beach.

06:57.217 --> 07:01.286
  I mean, it's not on the beach,
  but it's, you know,
  about ten minutes away,

07:01.288 --> 07:04.089
          and it's half as much
          as being at the water.

07:04.091 --> 07:05.624
               You all right?

07:05.626 --> 07:08.293
I'm just gonna give
Pam a quick call.

07:08.295 --> 07:09.561
        Oh, she's gonna be fine.

07:09.563 --> 07:11.129
I'll just be a minute.

07:12.766 --> 07:14.166
         Hello, Megan.

07:15.402 --> 07:17.669
       I thought that was you.
       (chuckles)

07:18.772 --> 07:20.872
                  I'm sorry, uh,
                  do I know you?

07:20.874 --> 07:22.274
               I'm Mark Holter.

07:22.276 --> 07:24.242
             Right.

07:24.244 --> 07:25.710
      Where's your horse?

07:26.814 --> 07:27.946
                   Excuse me?

07:27.948 --> 07:30.615
       Oh, just, Megan
       used to always say

07:30.617 --> 07:34.953
 that a knight on a big
 white stallion was gonna come
 and carry her away some day.

07:34.955 --> 07:36.922
       You remember that, Megan?

07:36.924 --> 07:38.623
          You used to act it out
          with your Barbies

07:38.625 --> 07:41.593
   and this little plastic horse
   with the broken tail.

07:41.595 --> 07:43.428
            I guess a cop was
            the next best thing.

07:43.430 --> 07:45.630
                    MARK:
                    I'm sorry.
                    Who are you?

07:45.632 --> 07:47.632
         Oh, sorry.
         Donnie Hamel.

07:47.634 --> 07:49.167
       Megan and I
       go way back.

07:49.169 --> 07:50.936
            Uh-huh.

07:50.938 --> 07:53.071
    How'd you know
    that I was a police officer?

07:53.073 --> 07:54.306
         Ah, Facebook.

07:54.308 --> 07:56.408
                       Oh. Yeah.
            Yeah.

07:56.410 --> 07:58.944
   It's scary to think about
   how our shit's out there
   for everyone to see, huh?

07:58.946 --> 08:00.445
                          Yeah.
         Oh, cute kid,
         by the way.

08:00.447 --> 08:02.080
                      Thank you.

08:02.082 --> 08:03.648
        So you--
        Do you live around here?

08:03.650 --> 08:06.184
     No, Officer, not for...
     not for years now.

08:06.186 --> 08:07.686
      I'm just back
      in town on business.

08:07.688 --> 08:09.754
      I'm the regional rep
      for Tire Outpost.

08:09.756 --> 08:13.158
   So, let me know when
   you need some new rubber,
   and I will hook you up.

08:13.160 --> 08:14.793
             All right. Will do.
           All right.

08:14.795 --> 08:17.796
 And you and I should
 get some coffee at some point.

08:17.798 --> 08:19.998
          I'm out at the Baymont
          by the interstate.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.133
  I'm sure you know the place.

08:22.135 --> 08:23.702
             Now...

08:23.704 --> 08:26.872
   anyway, I don't want
   to interrupt your dinner
   any longer.

08:26.874 --> 08:30.809
     You look great.
     And it was a pleasure
     to meet you, sir.

08:30.811 --> 08:33.345
            Yeah. Same here.

08:33.347 --> 08:35.013
     Okay. Enjoy your meal.

08:40.787 --> 08:41.953
            Should I be jealous?

08:41.955 --> 08:43.388
That's not funny.
                        (laughs)

08:43.390 --> 08:45.690
            There something
            wrong with that guy?

08:45.692 --> 08:47.459
Yeah, actually.

08:48.729 --> 08:51.029
He's an asshole.

08:51.031 --> 08:52.397
A dumb jock
and a bully,

08:52.399 --> 08:54.332
and I thought I'd never
have to see him again.

08:54.334 --> 08:56.034
                    Hmm.
    So...

08:57.137 --> 08:58.537
    You want me to kick his ass?

08:58.539 --> 09:02.073
No, but don't you dare
buy any tires from him.

09:02.075 --> 09:04.543
                  (laughs)

09:04.545 --> 09:06.578
      GILES:
      How do you want 'em?

09:06.580 --> 09:08.713
              MRS. OGDEN:
              Oh, I'll have mine
              still mooing.

09:08.715 --> 09:11.550
    You're eating meat?
    I got you garden burgers.

09:11.552 --> 09:15.420
     I just sort of started
     having a taste for it.

09:15.422 --> 09:17.022
        She keeps surprising me.

09:17.024 --> 09:19.658
          Secret to
          a successful marriage.

09:19.660 --> 09:23.028
After 32 years,
I don't think we have
any surprises left.

09:23.030 --> 09:24.829
    Oh, is that a challenge?

09:24.831 --> 09:28.333
Mmm, no, ma'am.
I know better than
to throw down with you.

09:28.335 --> 09:29.501
           (laughing)
        (dog whimpering)

09:29.503 --> 09:31.403
Oh, honey, would you
mind letting him out?

09:31.405 --> 09:33.038
    (barking and scratching
    at the door)

09:33.040 --> 09:34.105
           Come on.

09:34.107 --> 09:35.907
           (gasping)
           Oh!

09:35.909 --> 09:38.009
          Buzzy, stop!
          Buzzy, no!

09:38.011 --> 09:40.011
   (barking continues)
            I'm so sorry.

09:40.013 --> 09:41.379
What's wrong with you?

09:41.381 --> 09:42.681
What's wrong
with you, Buzzy?

09:42.683 --> 09:44.182
Come on, now, Buzzy.

09:44.184 --> 09:45.717
Buzzy, come on,
good boy.
          Sorry.

09:45.719 --> 09:47.218
GILES:
Good boy,
good boy, good boy.

09:47.220 --> 09:49.120
                  Good boy.
           (barking)

09:49.122 --> 09:51.256
 Lord have mercy, I don't know
 what got into him.

09:51.258 --> 09:53.959
    Oh, he's just letting us
    all know who's boss.

09:53.961 --> 09:56.027
           Anybody need anything
           from inside?

09:56.029 --> 09:57.529
                 Hit me.

09:57.531 --> 09:59.364
             You better
             slow down, big boy.

09:59.366 --> 10:01.166
                    Never.

10:02.869 --> 10:05.236
       I'll go help Rose
       with the drinks.

10:05.238 --> 10:07.739
Hey, I'm sorry about that.

10:07.741 --> 10:10.609
            They do say
            they're excellent
            judges of character.

10:10.611 --> 10:12.243
   Well, he sniffed you out.

10:12.245 --> 10:14.245
(chuckles)

10:14.247 --> 10:16.181
               Almost forgot.

10:21.822 --> 10:24.289
                 I'll be damned.

10:24.291 --> 10:26.324
That's yours, isn't it?

10:26.326 --> 10:29.628
       It sure is. I... never
       thought I'd see it again.

10:29.630 --> 10:31.129
How'd you lose it?

10:31.131 --> 10:33.064
       Oh, I don't rightly know.

10:33.066 --> 10:35.900
         Kat's always telling me
         not to wear it to work.

10:35.902 --> 10:38.036
       Could have been anywhere.

10:39.506 --> 10:40.739
           Where'd you find it?

10:40.741 --> 10:44.009
Someone turned it in
down at the station.

10:44.011 --> 10:47.045
It's good to know
we still got us some
honest folks out there.

10:56.990 --> 11:00.792
     (blues music playing)

11:00.794 --> 11:03.495
 ♪ My baby don't have to work ♪

11:05.465 --> 11:08.400
       ♪ She don't have
       to rob and steal ♪

11:13.040 --> 11:16.074
 ♪ My baby don't have to work ♪

11:17.878 --> 11:21.012
       ♪ She don't have
       to rob and steal ♪

11:25.152 --> 11:26.885
      ♪ 'Cause I give
      her everything... ♪

11:26.887 --> 11:29.187
         Hey.

11:29.189 --> 11:30.522
             What can I get you?

11:30.524 --> 11:35.126
Uh, just a beer.
I guess, a Bud.

11:35.128 --> 11:36.494
                      All right.

11:36.496 --> 11:37.796
Thanks.

11:39.166 --> 11:41.433
   ♪ She wrote me a letter ♪

11:43.136 --> 11:45.603
       ♪ She said she was
       coming home soon ♪

11:48.041 --> 11:51.409
Well, well, well,
look who it is.

11:53.046 --> 11:56.881
I'd say it was
a coincidence, you know,

11:56.883 --> 11:59.317
but given how small
this fucking town is,

11:59.319 --> 12:01.219
it'd probably be weirder
if I didn't see you.

12:02.422 --> 12:04.355
        What are you doing here?

12:04.357 --> 12:07.459
Just some new business,
some old business.

12:10.897 --> 12:13.531
Speaking of which,
I saw Megan today.
She looked good.

12:13.533 --> 12:15.667
                 Aah!

12:15.669 --> 12:17.335
    (grunting and shouting)

12:20.373 --> 12:22.006
   Okay! Okay!
            Get off!

12:22.008 --> 12:23.775
            Get off!

12:27.214 --> 12:28.446
                Keep it outside!

12:32.052 --> 12:33.451
So this is how
it's gonna be?

12:35.922 --> 12:37.088
                     Fuck you.

12:49.269 --> 12:51.302
           Stay down.

12:57.878 --> 12:58.943
             Shit.

13:00.280 --> 13:02.947
           (groaning)

13:08.255 --> 13:10.054
         Stay down,
         you dumb fuck!

13:18.965 --> 13:21.900
     You stay way from her.

13:21.902 --> 13:25.103
     Always trying
     to play the guardian angel.

13:25.105 --> 13:27.305
    Haven't you figured out
    they don't exist?

13:33.446 --> 13:34.746
             Fuck.

13:56.136 --> 13:58.536
  MAN (over radio):
  We got a little bit of gray
  sky in West Virginia today,

13:58.538 --> 14:00.438
      but that'll clear up
      this afternoon.

14:00.440 --> 14:02.607
 Here's a tune to put
 a little energy in your step.

14:02.609 --> 14:05.043
     (country music plays)

14:05.045 --> 14:07.779
   ♪ Well, everything's been
   a little complicated... ♪

14:07.781 --> 14:10.782
       (cell phone rings)

14:18.391 --> 14:20.124
                   Hello?

14:20.126 --> 14:22.360
    KYLE (over phone):
    Where are you? I've been
    calling you all morning.

14:22.362 --> 14:24.529
           Sorry. I didn't
           recognize the number.

14:24.531 --> 14:27.365
       KYLE:
       I got a new phone.
       Where are you?

14:27.367 --> 14:30.368
    I'm at the thrift store.
    What's wrong?

14:30.370 --> 14:33.004
 I ran into Donnie last night.

14:33.006 --> 14:35.974
     He said he saw you.
     Did something happen?

14:38.879 --> 14:40.378
             Megan?

14:42.983 --> 14:44.382
       Nothing happened.

14:44.384 --> 14:46.651
        I was at dinner
        and he, um...

14:48.088 --> 14:49.587
       Nothing happened.

14:49.589 --> 14:50.755
     KYLE:
     What are we gonna do?

14:50.757 --> 14:52.557
   We're not doing anything.

14:52.559 --> 14:54.058
       KYLE:
       Look, I can't
       just ignore this.

14:54.060 --> 14:56.060
     Yes, you can.
                 Megan.

14:56.062 --> 14:57.896
      Aren't you in enough
      trouble as it is?

14:57.898 --> 15:01.332
 The last thing you need to do
 is get mixed up with him.

15:02.535 --> 15:06.905
   MEGAN:
   You didn't, did you? Kyle?

15:06.907 --> 15:08.606
      I can't do nothing,
      you know that.

15:08.608 --> 15:10.108
      You've done enough.

15:11.378 --> 15:13.011
       Promise me, Kyle.

15:15.081 --> 15:17.081
           All right.

15:17.083 --> 15:20.018
    MEGAN:
    Thanks for checking in,
    shithead, but I'm fine.

15:20.020 --> 15:21.219
          But, Megan--

15:21.221 --> 15:22.754
          I gotta go.

15:22.756 --> 15:24.622
             Hey.

15:45.111 --> 15:47.145
I went by the church.

15:47.147 --> 15:50.248
Florence said
you was out here.

15:50.250 --> 15:52.550
           That woman
           cannot keep a secret.

15:54.554 --> 15:56.187
You been out here all day?

15:58.058 --> 16:00.024
    I have a confession to make.

16:01.828 --> 16:03.995
       One of the things
       that sucks about this job

16:03.997 --> 16:06.297
       is that everybody
       wants something from you.

16:07.400 --> 16:09.133
       Every misery they suffer,

16:09.135 --> 16:10.835
            every dying grandma,

16:10.837 --> 16:13.471
    every cheating husband,

16:13.473 --> 16:15.707
     all gets dumped on me.

16:17.077 --> 16:18.743
Sometimes I just need a break.

16:18.745 --> 16:20.478
Don't we all.

16:22.816 --> 16:24.482
        Come on. Give me a hand.

16:28.254 --> 16:30.655
       You tracked me down,
       so what can I do for you?

16:30.657 --> 16:33.758
Well, how's it
you get your...

16:33.760 --> 16:36.494
I don't know what
you call 'em, cases, victims?

16:36.496 --> 16:39.530
Is it like, you got
a bat phone in the church
or something?

16:39.532 --> 16:40.832
                      (chuckles)

16:40.834 --> 16:42.967
             Itching for
             some action, right?

16:42.969 --> 16:45.003
            Well...

16:45.005 --> 16:47.105
people close to me
get hurt,

16:47.107 --> 16:49.774
and it's been going on
a long time,

16:49.776 --> 16:52.276
and I think it might
still be going on.

16:52.278 --> 16:54.345
I don't feel like
sitting on my ass anymore.

16:54.347 --> 16:55.980
          You weren't sitting on
          your ass last night.

16:55.982 --> 16:58.149
                 I heard you got
                 knocked on it.

16:58.151 --> 17:00.485
That's old business.
It's got nothing
to do with this.

17:00.487 --> 17:02.720
            The hell it doesn't.

17:02.722 --> 17:05.556
    You got a gift, son,
    and I wanna help you use it.

17:05.558 --> 17:07.157
  But you also got a reputation.

17:07.160 --> 17:09.660
         People gotta be willing
         to let you in the door.

17:09.662 --> 17:12.463
      You wanna fight the devil,
      start by cleaning your
      fucking act up.

17:12.464 --> 17:13.865
You talk to God
with that mouth?

17:13.867 --> 17:15.366
          Oh, he's heard
          a lot worse than that.

17:18.471 --> 17:20.271
        Have any plans
        for the rest of the day?

17:21.540 --> 17:24.442
             Come on. Let's go
             for a little drive.

17:29.716 --> 17:31.315
Forgetting something?

17:31.317 --> 17:33.317
                Oh, thanks, hon.

17:35.488 --> 17:37.055
      Forgetting something else?

17:38.258 --> 17:39.624
                           Damn.

17:41.861 --> 17:44.195
               I'll see you
               in a couple days.

17:44.197 --> 17:46.330
                You put that on.
          Yes, ma'am.

17:46.332 --> 17:48.766
         I don't want one them
         dumb crackers mistaking
         you for a deer.

17:48.768 --> 17:52.403
Those dumb crackers
are our good friends
and neighbors.

17:57.610 --> 18:00.344
               The exorcism
               is a last resort.

18:00.346 --> 18:04.882
   My goal is to not
   have to perform another one.

18:04.884 --> 18:07.618
         And this fruit cocktail
         is your secret weapon?

18:07.620 --> 18:09.587
More like a vaccine.

18:09.589 --> 18:13.925
Our job is to... is to help
people resist the dark forces.

18:13.927 --> 18:16.094
            Deny the devil
            a foot in that door.

18:16.096 --> 18:17.261
            Uh-huh.

18:17.263 --> 18:18.863
    You got a problem with that?
        (doorbell rings)

18:18.865 --> 18:22.066
I just don't see how that
fits in to what happened
with my mom.

18:22.068 --> 18:24.068
Or my wife,
or Joshua Austin.

18:24.070 --> 18:27.805
I mean, what did they
ever do to let the devil in?

18:29.809 --> 18:31.542
                WOMAN:
                Hello, Reverend.

18:31.544 --> 18:34.112
     Sophie, I didn't
     know you were in town.

18:34.114 --> 18:36.647
           Just for the weekend,
           to see Mama.

18:36.649 --> 18:38.116
                        Come in.

18:44.624 --> 18:47.625
    This is Kyle.
    He's helping me
    with the shut-ins today.

18:47.627 --> 18:49.127
               Nice to meet you,
               I'm Sophie.

18:49.129 --> 18:50.228
        Ma'am.

18:50.230 --> 18:51.896
          Mmm, please, no ma'am.

18:51.898 --> 18:53.397
        Oh.

18:53.399 --> 18:54.832
    And how is your mother?

18:54.834 --> 18:57.401
          Um... I'm not so sure.

18:59.172 --> 19:01.506
       Well, what is it?

19:01.508 --> 19:03.141
        Can I talk to you alone?

19:17.590 --> 19:19.490
        I can't do this anymore.

19:20.426 --> 19:22.827
    She used to be so sweet.

19:22.829 --> 19:25.463
   When the kids were little,
   she just doted on 'em.

19:25.465 --> 19:27.598
        They just loved
        to come visit their Oma.

19:27.600 --> 19:31.035
      But now...
      she's a cranky old bitch.

19:31.037 --> 19:34.272
Well, she always
has been a character.

19:34.274 --> 19:36.507
              No, she's changed.

19:36.509 --> 19:39.343
We all change, Sophie,
I mean, um...

19:43.216 --> 19:45.216
          (screaming)

19:47.187 --> 19:49.287
I still think of myself
as a 20-year-old buck,

19:49.289 --> 19:50.655
    and then I look
    at myself in the mirror,

19:50.657 --> 19:52.857
and I don't recognize that
old fart staring back at me.

19:52.859 --> 19:56.360
 No. It's the things she says.

19:56.362 --> 20:00.798
    It's the foul bile
    that comes out of her mouth.

20:00.800 --> 20:05.002
       She called my 13-year-old
       daughter a whore.

20:05.004 --> 20:08.472
        It's like the devil's
        got ahold of her tongue.
Somebody out there?

20:08.474 --> 20:10.241
Who is it?

20:13.346 --> 20:16.881
        (clock chiming)

20:21.921 --> 20:23.721
I'm with the reverend.

20:23.723 --> 20:25.523
              Well, get in here.

20:25.525 --> 20:27.058
             Ma'am.

20:27.060 --> 20:29.427
       We're dropping off
       your groceries.
       I'm Kyle Barnes.

20:29.429 --> 20:31.596
      I know who you are.

20:35.935 --> 20:37.735
    Pity about your mother.

20:37.737 --> 20:41.172
            Oh. Um... thank you.

20:41.174 --> 20:42.607
               It's a nice place
               you got here.

20:42.609 --> 20:44.408
          Used to be.

20:44.410 --> 20:48.980
      But everything goes
      to shit eventually.

20:51.217 --> 20:53.150
      Like your marriage.

20:55.188 --> 20:57.688
 Hard to keep
 a romance alive

20:57.690 --> 21:00.725
  once you start
  throwing punches, isn't it?

21:00.727 --> 21:01.926
             Okay.

21:01.928 --> 21:04.028
What about
the Austin boy?

21:04.030 --> 21:07.064
        I saw his face.

21:07.066 --> 21:09.867
     You, uh, you can't seem
     to help yourself.

21:12.772 --> 21:14.805
    I think I'm gonna go get
    the reverend for you.

21:14.807 --> 21:16.641
        What'd you see?

21:16.643 --> 21:17.775
                       What?

21:17.777 --> 21:19.744
         With the boy?

21:19.746 --> 21:21.812
   When you did that to him,

21:21.814 --> 21:23.547
        what'd you see?

21:31.157 --> 21:32.556
            (scoffs)

21:36.929 --> 21:38.329
       Here. Let me help.

21:38.331 --> 21:39.764
   (screams) Oh!

21:39.766 --> 21:41.132
                   Are you okay?

21:41.134 --> 21:43.401
  Don't touch me! Don't!
           All right, all right.

21:43.403 --> 21:44.669
What happened?
                           Mama?

21:44.671 --> 21:45.770
           She fell.

21:45.772 --> 21:48.072
    Oh...
     All right. Let me help you.

21:48.074 --> 21:49.407
          Come on. Take it easy.

21:49.409 --> 21:51.742
   All right, Mildred,
   I got you.

21:51.744 --> 21:53.177
     Oh.
         There you go.

21:53.179 --> 21:55.313
   (groaning)

21:56.582 --> 22:00.518
God bless your
kind soul, Reverend.

22:00.520 --> 22:04.021
You know I appreciate
your help so much.

22:08.194 --> 22:12.163
       But I'm not up
       for a visit today.

22:20.373 --> 22:21.839
What happened in there?

22:21.841 --> 22:24.775
         She was asking me
         questions about Joshua,

22:24.777 --> 22:26.477
               about what we saw
               that night.

22:26.479 --> 22:28.446
I'm not surprised.

22:28.448 --> 22:30.981
People are always
looking for lurid details.

22:30.983 --> 22:33.284
When she fell,
I went to help her,

22:33.286 --> 22:36.387
and when I touched her,
she reacted just like Joshua,

22:36.389 --> 22:38.322
and Blake.

22:38.324 --> 22:40.658
She's one of 'em,
isn't she?

22:40.660 --> 22:42.560
She's one of the ones
you exorcised.

22:45.164 --> 22:47.198
            About two years ago.

22:49.001 --> 22:52.036
    Took me almost a week
    to drive the demon from her.

22:52.038 --> 22:55.239
And? Was it like with Joshua?
Did you see it come out?

22:55.241 --> 22:57.975
      I told you,
      it's not always like that.

22:57.977 --> 22:59.577
Then how can you
be sure it's gone?

22:59.579 --> 23:02.079
            Because I have faith
            in the power of God
            over the devil.

23:03.816 --> 23:05.649
            Things change, Kyle.
            People get old.

23:05.651 --> 23:08.018
         Sometimes we lose
         something of ourselves.

23:08.020 --> 23:11.322
   But that lady's been sitting
   in the front pew of my church
   for the past two years,

23:11.324 --> 23:14.024
          singing hymns
          and praising the Lord.

23:14.026 --> 23:16.627
  I hope I'd know
  if I was preaching to a demon.

23:26.406 --> 23:29.673
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:58.237 --> 24:00.671
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:44.584 --> 24:46.250
  Hey.
                   Hey.

24:47.520 --> 24:48.752
It smells good.

24:48.754 --> 24:51.088
          Don't get too excited.
          Franks and beans.

24:51.090 --> 24:53.290
     Oh.

24:53.292 --> 24:55.426
I thought we were
having leftover pasta.

24:55.428 --> 24:57.761
      Eh. I didn't feel like it.

24:57.763 --> 25:01.298
Sure you didn't just eat it
all for yourself for lunch?

25:01.300 --> 25:04.869
      Yeah, Mark, I wolfed down
      all your fettuccine so you
      couldn't have any.

25:08.541 --> 25:10.608
How was your day?

25:10.610 --> 25:12.576
                 The usual. You?

25:13.946 --> 25:15.412
           The usual.

25:18.951 --> 25:20.784
Dinner last night was nice.

25:21.854 --> 25:23.487
                   It was.

25:23.489 --> 25:26.991
I think we should do it
more often, you know?
It's good for us.

25:26.993 --> 25:28.726
Having time alone.

25:30.496 --> 25:32.863
You know, I worry sometimes
when we just don't talk...

25:32.865 --> 25:34.532
            enough.

25:34.534 --> 25:36.300
          Welcome to parenthood.

25:36.302 --> 25:38.135
Yeah.

25:38.137 --> 25:40.971
   And every dinner out costs us
   a week of franks and beans.

25:40.973 --> 25:42.606
Yeah, well,
I think it's worth it.

25:45.344 --> 25:49.046
So, I'm your knight
in shining armor, huh?

25:49.048 --> 25:50.548
                           What?

25:50.550 --> 25:53.083
I think it's kinda sweet,
you never told me about it,

25:53.085 --> 25:59.123
but didn't know you used
to dream of having a hero
on a white stallion.

26:01.494 --> 26:03.994
You know, it's a good thing
I rode into town.

26:03.996 --> 26:05.663
              You think that's
              why I married you?

26:05.665 --> 26:07.498
            'Cause you're a cop?

26:07.500 --> 26:09.500
           What? No.

26:09.502 --> 26:11.869
         You think I just wanted
         someone to protect me?

26:11.871 --> 26:13.604
No, that's not what I said.

26:13.606 --> 26:16.674
  It's insulting.
  I don't want to hear it again.

26:16.676 --> 26:18.409
          No problem.

26:18.411 --> 26:20.611
MEGAN:
Holly, dinner!

26:20.613 --> 26:21.979
            (sighs)

26:27.887 --> 26:30.354
        (clock ticking)

26:58.718 --> 27:02.620
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:19.772 --> 27:23.207
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:09.021 --> 28:12.856
   (TV playing indistinctly)

28:35.381 --> 28:37.581
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:38.611 --> 29:41.211
         (siren chirps)

29:42.715 --> 29:43.947
            Hop in.

29:46.051 --> 29:47.484
  How long is this gonna take?

29:47.486 --> 29:48.952
          It depends.

29:50.122 --> 29:51.822
I got stuff that needs
to go in the freezer.

29:51.824 --> 29:54.792
         Look, if your ice cream
         gets soft, I'll buy you
         another quart.

29:54.794 --> 29:56.026
            Get in.

30:07.940 --> 30:09.239
                Keep the change.

30:19.285 --> 30:22.486
     That used to be your label.
     Something change?

30:22.488 --> 30:25.622
  Uh, it's...

30:25.624 --> 30:28.258
It's been a while since
we done this is all.

30:28.260 --> 30:30.994
      Yeah, well,
      there's a reason for that.

30:30.996 --> 30:33.330
Look, Mark, I'm...
                We need to talk.

30:33.332 --> 30:36.867
trying to keep my head down. but
I shouldn't have lost my cool.

30:36.869 --> 30:38.936
        I don't even wanna know.

30:40.673 --> 30:43.774
                 Look, um...

30:43.776 --> 30:47.778
  Megan and I, we went to dinner
  the other night. Date night.

30:47.780 --> 30:49.880
       You know, we got a sitter
       and the whole deal.

30:49.882 --> 30:52.015
Oh. Okay. Sounds nice.

30:52.017 --> 30:54.518
          Yeah, well,
          it was supposed to be.

30:54.520 --> 30:57.187
    'Til this guy came up
    to the table and said, "hi."

30:58.557 --> 31:01.458
     Said he was a tire salesman
     from out of town.

31:04.730 --> 31:06.463
               Donnie something?

31:07.867 --> 31:10.167
    You know anything about him?

31:10.169 --> 31:11.301
         No.

31:12.671 --> 31:14.404
            Damn it, Kyle,
            don't you lie to me.

31:14.406 --> 31:16.206
     Mark.

31:16.208 --> 31:18.475
                    Is that him?

31:18.477 --> 31:20.410
                      I knew it.

31:31.590 --> 31:33.357
How much did she tell you?

31:33.359 --> 31:36.460
   Just that he was a foster kid
   her parents took in, and...

31:39.498 --> 31:41.064
       and he abused her.

31:42.534 --> 31:44.501
               She never told me
               his name.

31:44.503 --> 31:47.304
   Motherfucker told me himself.

31:48.841 --> 31:50.374
               He literally came
               right up to me.

31:50.376 --> 31:53.076
               He said,
               "Hi, I'm Donnie."

31:56.749 --> 31:58.148
He say anything else?

31:59.952 --> 32:01.251
                No.

32:03.589 --> 32:06.757
         Just that he and Megan,
         they went <i> way</i> back.

32:13.032 --> 32:15.232
When I found out
what he was doing,

32:15.234 --> 32:17.267
I started sleeping
on the floor in her room.

32:18.871 --> 32:22.873
I couldn't...
couldn't fight back
and win or nothing.

32:24.243 --> 32:27.277
I could get in the way,
take a beating.

32:27.279 --> 32:29.446
I was an old pro at that.

32:29.448 --> 32:31.381
       I thought Megan
       made that whole thing up.

32:31.383 --> 32:33.517
             Just to defend you.

32:35.087 --> 32:37.220
         After everything
         with Allison and Amber.

32:38.657 --> 32:40.223
                  Oh, man.

32:47.499 --> 32:49.299
She wants us to let it be.

32:59.979 --> 33:01.712
Thanks for the drink.

33:16.762 --> 33:22.065
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:17.489 --> 34:20.757
   Well, this is a surprise.

34:20.759 --> 34:22.458
       You have to leave.

34:23.996 --> 34:25.362
I was just on my way out.

34:25.364 --> 34:27.264
         You have to leave town.

34:29.835 --> 34:33.235
   Okay, I'm sorry, Megan,
   but I have business here.

34:33.237 --> 34:34.670
                   I don't care.

34:38.277 --> 34:39.576
       Let's talk inside.

34:43.782 --> 34:45.949
             Sure.

34:45.951 --> 34:47.617
       Got a few minutes.

35:05.904 --> 35:08.338
          You want a glass
          of water or something?

35:15.747 --> 35:18.215
      (coughs)

35:18.217 --> 35:20.951
Look, I shouldn't have
interrupted your dinner
the other night.

35:20.953 --> 35:22.953
I'm sorry about that.

35:22.955 --> 35:25.622
    I'm not here 'cause
    you messed up my date night.

35:27.826 --> 35:30.627
               In the same house
               was too close.

35:30.629 --> 35:33.997
        In the same town
        is too close.

35:33.999 --> 35:35.499
        You need to go.

35:35.501 --> 35:37.734
Hey, look, we both
have to deal with
what happened back then.

35:37.736 --> 35:39.503
                        (scoffs)
                        Are--

35:39.505 --> 35:41.805
                Are you serious?

35:41.807 --> 35:43.006
       Yeah.

35:44.243 --> 35:47.310
Look, I was
a fucked up kid, Megan.

35:47.312 --> 35:50.580
That doesn't excuse it,
but it is what it is.

35:50.582 --> 35:53.016
I'm not that kid anymore.
Okay? People change.

35:53.018 --> 35:55.852
 There's no way
 you could ever change enough.

35:57.289 --> 35:59.322
You know, it cost me, too.

35:59.324 --> 36:03.827
After I got kicked out of
the house, I wound back up
in the County Children's home.

36:03.829 --> 36:07.097
Who's gonna want to take in
a kid with that on his
record, huh?

36:07.099 --> 36:08.965
        Is that why you're here?

36:08.967 --> 36:12.569
         To mess with my head
         'cause you're fucked up
         life is my fault?

36:12.571 --> 36:14.704
        No.

36:14.706 --> 36:16.673
Megan, I'm here
to sell tires.

36:18.377 --> 36:21.478
But actions do
have consequences.

36:21.480 --> 36:23.547
     Mine and yours.

36:23.549 --> 36:28.485
 You think this haunts me.
 That's what you want to hear.

36:28.487 --> 36:31.288
      That because of you,
      I'm broken.

36:31.290 --> 36:32.756
            (scoffs)

36:33.959 --> 36:37.060
      You arrogant prick.

36:37.062 --> 36:39.529
     You're nothing to me.

36:39.531 --> 36:41.731
      A bump in the road.

36:41.733 --> 36:46.269
    Something I scraped off
    my shoe a long time ago.

36:49.708 --> 36:52.342
         Tire salesman.

36:52.344 --> 36:55.912
Then ask yourself why
you're here, Megan,

36:55.914 --> 36:59.249
in my hotel room,
all by yourself.

37:00.719 --> 37:05.322
You see, maybe
I am more than a bump
in the road to you.

37:06.992 --> 37:10.927
Maybe I do... haunt you.

37:12.231 --> 37:14.197
 I'm here to protect my family.

37:14.199 --> 37:17.000
 'Cause if my husband
 ever finds out who you are...

37:19.871 --> 37:23.840
 I won't let him ruin his life
 over a meaningless piece
 of shit like you.

37:25.010 --> 37:26.910
         Over nothing.

37:26.912 --> 37:31.248
       (doorbell ringing)

37:31.250 --> 37:32.849
                   Quit ringing!

37:32.851 --> 37:35.752
      I'm not exactly
      Speedy Gonzales, you know.

37:35.754 --> 37:37.721
I'm sorry, Mildred.

37:37.723 --> 37:40.056
Is Sophie not here?

37:40.058 --> 37:41.524
               Went out.

37:41.526 --> 37:45.195
     Can't stand being cooped up
     with me all day, I guess.

37:45.197 --> 37:47.631
         Probably dying
         to get back to Houston.

37:47.633 --> 37:48.965
May I come in?

37:52.738 --> 37:54.504
           I suppose.

38:01.380 --> 38:04.314
    I wanted to check in
    after that little, um...

38:05.417 --> 38:06.883
      incident yesterday.

38:06.885 --> 38:09.953
That was your friend's doing,
not yours.

38:11.957 --> 38:13.390
          What happened exactly?

38:13.392 --> 38:15.091
    I tripped.

38:15.093 --> 38:17.394
Lucky I didn't
break my other hip.

38:17.396 --> 38:19.462
                Praise the Lord.

38:22.100 --> 38:24.968
              Sophie says, uh...

38:24.970 --> 38:28.638
     says that you don't
     enjoy visiting with
     your grandchildren anymore?

38:30.509 --> 38:32.309
                 That seems sad.

38:33.445 --> 38:35.845
They used to be cute.

38:37.983 --> 38:40.350
One of 'em's going
off to law school,

38:40.352 --> 38:43.153
and the girl, she's--
all she wants to do
is whore around.

38:43.155 --> 38:46.089
What's cute about that?

38:46.091 --> 38:48.591
          Well, that's certainly
          a change in attitude.

38:48.593 --> 38:50.660
They changed, Reverend.

38:50.662 --> 38:53.396
Why does everyone expect
me to stay the same?

38:55.267 --> 38:58.101
          Nothing wrong
          with mixing things up,

38:58.103 --> 38:59.402
                      but, um...

39:00.706 --> 39:03.106
          some things are fine
          just the way they are.

39:04.710 --> 39:08.378
          Like, we used
          to sit here for hours,

39:08.380 --> 39:11.881
           you and I playing
           Scrabble, backgammon.

39:13.185 --> 39:14.784
      Why'd that have to change?

39:16.555 --> 39:20.190
I don't know how much
time I've got left, Reverend.

39:22.527 --> 39:26.296
I'm tired of playing
games with you.

39:27.499 --> 39:28.565
          (screeches)

39:29.968 --> 39:32.068
          Ha! Gotcha.

39:33.004 --> 39:34.671
          (chuckling)

39:34.673 --> 39:36.373
Oh...

39:37.709 --> 39:40.043
What if we like
who we've become?

39:40.045 --> 39:43.880
What if it works
better for us this way?

39:43.882 --> 39:48.151
           How can it be better
           to hurt the people
           who want to help you?

39:49.588 --> 39:52.722
           To reject their love?

39:52.724 --> 39:54.424
                 To leave a hole
                 in their soul?

39:54.426 --> 39:59.229
Holes can be filled.

39:59.231 --> 40:05.268
There's room inside
a human soul for
so much more, Reverend.

40:05.270 --> 40:08.605
More than love,
more than God.

40:08.607 --> 40:12.809
Something that feeds it
in ways you haven't imagined.

40:17.382 --> 40:20.950
Oh. I changed my mind.

40:20.952 --> 40:26.456
I do love our little games.
How 'bout some Scrabble, hmm?

40:32.397 --> 40:36.399
          (urinating)

40:36.401 --> 40:38.501
             Ahh...

40:43.608 --> 40:45.008
      (branches snapping)

41:47.772 --> 41:51.708
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:25.076 --> 42:26.142
                      Hey.

42:29.214 --> 42:31.481
Know what my favorite sin is?

42:31.483 --> 42:34.684
        You have a favorite sin?

42:34.686 --> 42:38.021
     Everybody goes
     for lust or wrath.

42:38.023 --> 42:39.822
They're the sexy ones.

42:39.824 --> 42:44.327
          Yeah, well, "lust."
          It's kinda baked right
          in there, isn't it?

42:44.329 --> 42:48.831
Pride. Pride's the bad boy.

42:48.833 --> 42:53.102
It sneaks up on you,
because it doesn't feel
like a sin.

42:54.539 --> 42:56.339
What's wrong with
feeling good about yourself?

42:56.341 --> 42:58.541
Taking pride
in a job well done?

42:58.543 --> 43:01.210
             Yeah, and you start
             getting used to it.

43:01.212 --> 43:03.479
  You don't notice
  when the job wasn't done well.

43:05.083 --> 43:06.950
That's right.

43:08.520 --> 43:11.120
And there's a job
that I didn't do well.

43:12.757 --> 43:14.190
       I'll get my coat.

43:40.485 --> 43:42.185
        (doorbell rings)

43:45.657 --> 43:47.056
        What are you doing here?

43:47.058 --> 43:49.125
  Sorry it's so late.
  Is Mildred still awake?

43:49.127 --> 43:51.160
     Why do you want to see her?
It's a spiritual matter.

43:51.162 --> 43:52.629
           You think she's
           spitting up pea soup,

43:52.631 --> 43:54.564
     head spinning around,
     floating up to the ceiling?

43:54.566 --> 43:56.499
   Sophie, there's something
   you don't know about
   your mother.

43:56.501 --> 43:58.401
         That she was
         possessed by the devil

43:58.403 --> 44:00.770
              and that you tried
              to exorcise her
              two years ago.

44:00.772 --> 44:02.672
I didn't want to worry you.
We thought we dealt with it--

44:02.674 --> 44:04.674
       Dealt with it?
       Well, she finally told me
       what you did.

44:04.676 --> 44:06.809
      Locking her up for days,
      starving her, beating her,

44:06.811 --> 44:08.845
               beating the devil
               out of her.
    That's not her talking.

44:08.847 --> 44:11.314
     Then you show up here
     with this monster. Yeah,
     she told me about you, too.

44:11.316 --> 44:13.850
     What you did to that little
     boy and your own daughter.
    Sophie, listen to me--

44:13.852 --> 44:16.152
           Get out! You stay way
           from my mother.
   It's still inside of her.

44:16.154 --> 44:17.654
Let's go.
  Sophie, she needs our help.

44:17.656 --> 44:19.155
    I am calling the police.

44:22.761 --> 44:24.093
  I can't leave her like this.

44:34.439 --> 44:36.239
Small boy.
          Rev.

44:55.960 --> 44:57.393
     Okay.

45:02.233 --> 45:04.967
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:22.253 --> 45:25.154
         (siren blares)

45:42.507 --> 45:44.407
             Shit.

46:13.238 --> 46:15.772
    Not sure what
    the problem is, Officer.

46:19.778 --> 46:22.612
Mark, hey.

46:22.614 --> 46:24.447
    Step out of the car, please.

46:26.151 --> 46:28.117
Come on, man,
it's a rental.

46:28.119 --> 46:30.419
So, if there's a tail light
out or something it's not
my fault--

46:30.421 --> 46:31.721
      Step out of the car.

46:40.431 --> 46:44.367
      Put your hands on the car,
      legs apart.

46:49.307 --> 46:52.742
You know, I want you to just
think about this for a second.

46:52.744 --> 46:55.945
I mean, seriously, just--
just think about Megan,

46:55.947 --> 46:58.047
and think about that pretty
little girl of yours.

47:04.756 --> 47:07.023
       Mark, this is a bad idea.

47:07.025 --> 47:08.491
              Aah!

47:19.804 --> 47:22.872
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

47:34.385 --> 47:36.786
        (phone buzzing)

47:41.960 --> 47:43.693
     Hey, Chief, what's up?

47:43.695 --> 47:46.963
What did you do with
the evidence we collected
from the camper we found?

47:46.965 --> 47:49.165
            Boxed it up
            like you told me to.

47:49.167 --> 47:50.633
       You said you were
       going to take care of it.

47:50.635 --> 47:52.335
GILES:
I know what I said.

47:52.337 --> 47:54.904
First thing tomorrow morning,
I want you to ship it out
for analysis.

47:54.906 --> 47:57.573
The blood, the fibers,
all of it.

47:57.575 --> 47:59.542
The case is still open.

47:59.544 --> 48:01.110
        MARK: Yes, sir.

48:33.278 --> 48:34.844
          Hey.

48:39.384 --> 48:40.816
Heard you talking.

48:41.920 --> 48:44.387
        That was just the chief.

48:44.389 --> 48:46.222
         Talking about
         some work for tomorrow.

48:46.224 --> 48:47.990
Everything okay?

48:49.527 --> 48:51.260
   Yeah, it's just the usual.

48:54.866 --> 48:56.232
       Is Holly sleeping?

48:56.234 --> 48:58.234
      Yeah. Finally.

48:58.236 --> 49:02.939
Little drama, but I think
she was just overtired.

49:07.045 --> 49:08.678
        Sorry I'm late.

49:10.114 --> 49:13.249
 It's okay.
 There's lasagna in the fridge.

49:13.251 --> 49:14.884
   I can warm it up for you.

49:16.554 --> 49:20.189
     Nah, I'm okay. Thanks.

49:23.294 --> 49:24.794
       How was your day?

49:29.467 --> 49:31.300
             Usual.

49:45.149 --> 49:46.649
Damn it!

49:46.651 --> 49:48.084
God fucking damn it!

49:48.086 --> 49:50.653
         I'm a sucker!

49:50.655 --> 49:53.923
What if-- What if she's
not the only one?

49:53.925 --> 49:56.359
 You sat and played
 board games with Mildred
 for two years,

49:56.361 --> 49:58.094
     and you didn't have a clue.

49:59.697 --> 50:01.597
          What if it's
          the same with Allison?

50:04.869 --> 50:06.335
      Turn the car around.

50:06.337 --> 50:08.504
                 Kyle--
I gotta see my wife.

50:08.506 --> 50:11.774
     I understand, but you can't
     just go charging in there.

50:11.776 --> 50:13.776
   You were about ready
   to kick in Mildred's door.

50:13.778 --> 50:16.012
Mildred doesn't have
a restraining order on me!

50:21.519 --> 50:23.019
             Shit.

50:23.021 --> 50:24.787
       (tires screeching)

50:34.632 --> 50:38.401
              <i> ♪ ♪</i>

52:34.285 --> 52:36.285
          (screaming)

